caption: Had good fish and chips, and discovered a columbard wine, Mont Gravet, which I will be drinking again.  I liked it as much as I like well made sancerre wines.  If I lived in the neighborhood, I would eat at Baby Wale often.

Originally wanted the fish and chips but they ran out...a blessing in disguise!  Second choice was the pork ribs. Ummm glad they ran out of f&c. The ribs best I've ever had. Came with cabbage which was lightly dressed was simply a perfect combo.
One of the worse bartenders I’ve ever encountered. Place is nice but service is badddddd.

Sat at the bar on a Saturday night. Salami pizza was great and the drinks were great. The service, however, was absolutely terrible. The bartender finally took our order after 10 minutes of us sitting down. I would have love to drink more but the bartender never came back. We had to walk over to her at the other end of the bar and ask for the check after about 50 minutes of our first interaction. We were also two of about maybe 20 people in the whole place.

This place is eclectic, has a good location, and a very nice interior. The dining are and bar are quite nice, with high ceilings and plenty of space. The menu threw me off a bit, it was all over the place and very confusing, it's hard to believe their kitchen do all those diverse dishes justice. Everything we ordered was quality though, the "spring rolls", fried chicken, and fish n chips. What was the kicker for me was the service. Not the servers fault but it seemed like they only had 3 or so people working on a Friday night, led to long delays, some mistakes in drink orders. It's also strange that when we tried to split the check they said they could only do even splits. I'm not sure which POS they use, but every one I've used or seen is very capable of splitting customers checks, just a matter of the user knowing how.

Was visiting from out of town and this was close to my hotel. Great tasting beers on tap. Also the tomato soup and the mushroom pizza that were part of the happy hour special were fantastic. I would definitely return to this place.

Went on Tuesday night. Ribs were very good. Menu is unique - which is a good thing. Service friendly and professional(Pinky) but no host(ess) at front to seat you?? Had to go to bar. Would come back again if in area.  GoGo music theme is great especially for visitor here on biz.

Baby Wale has a lovely incredible long marble bar. It's nice for a cocktail but their food isn't really anything to rave about. I loved their potato leek soup but they've taken it off the menu. They have an eclectic mix of steak, papusas, sorry of random things and none particularly stands out. I would eat elsewhere and drink at the bar.

I tried the Salami pizza, the salami was regular but the mozzarella cheese they use for the pizza was amazing! The pie size is average, it is a thin crispy crust, but it it is full of flavor one. I really enjoyed it. Their beer selection is awesome as well, I had a really nice Red Ale and I have to say I am really happy with the service.

Very weird food. I personally don’t know how you would categorize this. Walked in and the place was dead on new year’s eve. I was confused at first but after we ate (and waited 30 mins for our food when we were one out of two tables there) I realized why. The menu was all over the place and me and my date’s dish was just plain right unappetizing. And don’t come here on a first date, the music is....interesting to say the least and doesn’t quite set the mood.

DONT BOTHER. My partner and I walked in and we were wondering around for ages trying to find someone to seat us. We approached a member of staff behind the bar, he said he’d get us seated and then just walked off leaving us there for ages whilst he mingled with staff in the kitchen and pottered around. No urgency or care in the world. We walked out and went to eat at Corduroy next door, great service, seated straight away, about 3 different members of staff came to check we were ok. Delicious food. Go there instead.
Fun bar with decent Spanish wines on special
Great food!
good wine and eats
Always a treat. Not even the noise level will get on the way of a tasty meal. Love the ribs!

Baby Wale claims to take bar food to a new level. Unfortunately that level is below whatever you will be imagining when you walk in the place.  The management seems to be singularly focused on avoiding the needs of the customers.  Finally, the portions are TINY. Definitely plan on going out to eat after your "dinner" at Baby Wale.
Great food
Great drinks and menu. Easy access to the convention center.
It was ok, nothing to write home about.
Worst service, waited for 15 minutes and no one even asked if we wanted a drink, we had to leave
Great place for a private reception upstairs. So tough to get a bartender's attention down below, even on a weeknight.

After a frosty start with a surly barman, which initially put us off ordering food, we were then greeted with a new waiter who transformed our evening and experience. The food was amazing, cooked to perfection and generous portions. So what started out as a potential disaster,  ended up being a fantastic evening and well worth the visit.
This place did not disappoint. The atmosphere was very cool and the food/beer selection is very impressive. The food that we got tasted Amazing and I HIGHLY recommend!!!!

It's nice inside but the food is... Weird. I thought it'd be pub food as described, but it's weird combinations, there's not a burger on the menu, but there is a $10 hot dog. Beer selection is mediocre, cocktails are okay, but the vibe is very much pub, so hopefully they get it together.
It was awesome

Been there only once, the atmosphere is good and drinks where ok, service was attentive and helpful, there was a small mistake in our check which was swiftly solved... Not the best bar but a good one, definitely worth a visit
(Translated by Google) The fried chicken is awesome! !! Space is also comfortable  (Original) 炸雞超棒的！！空間也很舒適
Was an after party spot so hard to judge as it was nearly empty at 10. Honestly one of the worst gin and tonics I've had
Asparagus salad was very good.
Very convenient if you are at the convention center.
Food was pretty unsatisfying and a cockroach ran across the bar....
The food was good. The service... Not so much. A small improvement in service would make this a decent dinner stop.
Nice drinks friendly service convenintly located close to Convention Center
Outstanding place. Its a great staple for DC. All the best in the near future.

Wanted a local restaurant with good food and it didn't disappoint! The fried chicken and fries meal tastes amazing. The fries are seasoned and perfect without ketchup. The chicken was cooked perfectly and the breading was great. The waitress/bartender working was quick and efficient and very friendly. Pricing is fair.
If you want drinks, go. If you want food, stay far far away.
Pretty hip spot conveniently located near DC convention center

We had a poor experience at this restaurant. The kitchen was painfully slow and still managed to get our order wrong. The restaurant was not crowded at the time, so there is no excuse. The food here was not good enough to justify the time or money.
Happy hour was excellent.  Food and drinks were top tier.  Great stop during Awesome Con.
(Translated by Google) The pizza is great.  (Original) La pizza genial.
Atmosphere is nice but the service was terrible.
Food was great! Server was super nice! I saw the bartender throw a reicpt at a customer .he continued to prance around smiling and laughing like it was ok. Because of that I will never return
Delicious food and amazing service!
Gogo music, friendly staff, not a bad happy hour. Enjoyed the eclectic food options, especially the zucchini pupusas!
Food good, service not so much.
Insufficient staff. Took ages to get a drink.
It was fine, but it was packed and the staff seemed overwhelmed trying to keep up.
Beautiful atmosphere
food and bev is great.  service = meh
One of my favorite places! I even through my birthday party here.
Just had drinks here, but very much like the long bar design. Certainly coming back here.
Good
Great atmosphere

I came here because it’s close to where I’m staying and I desperately needed a creamy, chocolate dessert! Whenever I have a dessert craving, I crave of what THIS  ended up being. What I dream of. So, thank you Baby Wale! What a delight! BTW, it's enough (dark) chocolate custard for 3-4 people! It's decadent and dreamy. It's a great atmosphere with live music

A little pricey and loud, service time was fair (not great) and although the waiter was very friendly, we did not see much of him. Otherwise the menu variations were excellent, we loved the old soda styles and the food was great.
Great atmosphere, but you have to order the right dish. The Chicken and waffles are worth the visit.
Nice folks, excellent beers.
Delicious food, poor service.
Great customer service. The young lady serving was polite even when someone broke a glass of beer. She was still understanding and respectful of her customers.
Casual pub environment. The service was excellent as was the food. If I lived here I would go back. Prices are moderate.
Great selection of beer and awesome service
Wonderful service, very salty Fried Chicken, halibut fish and chips was on point, peanut butter cookies amazing, peach tart extremely good.
Great atmosphere, great service, great drinks and great food.
Good place for social gatherings
Amazingly slow service!
Great drinks
Cool lil spot.
Great place with an extensive whiskey/bourbon menu.

This place is really great! They have a super agreeable happy hour pricing for drinks, and the food is wonderful. We got the pizza, fried chicken, and the fried rolls. All were amazing. The plates are pretty big, so I'd recommend sharing. But if I'm ever in downtown DC again, I'll come here!  Also the staff are super nice and the decor and atmosphere are great! ❤️
This place was amazing. Was with a big group and we all had a taste of the fried chicken, pizza, lobster roll and meatballs: all of it was phenomenal. Huge drink selection too!
Still one of my favorite places to go to after work in DC.  Fried chicken or pork ribs are both great options.
Great food and music
The food was fairly good, but not outstanding. Drinks were varied and well made. Atmosphere a little dead for a weekend but perhaps that was the weather. A solid choice for a quieter night out.
Ode to Go-Go. Glad to see DC culture honored here. Plus the cocktails and food is unique and delicious. Highly recommend!
Nothing special, but solid.
Great little place for a bite to eat

Terrific bar and grill! Great old decor with large bar and upstairs area for parties etc. The food is excellent and ranges from small appetizers to pizza, steak and salad choices. The bar has a good selection of beers and wines on the drink menu. Staff is friendly and service is good. All in all, a nice place for dinner or meeting friends for drinks.
Nice space, but just a heads up no TV's for better or for worse.
Great upstairs event space. Decent drink selection. Friendly service. Love the appetizers and Caesar salad.
The drinks weren't good.
Great venue to book a party at!
Had a great time.  Endless free appetizers brought around

My company hosted an event there. Great atmosphere from the setting, and had a great happy hour selection (corporate package). Can get pretty loud for a corporate event, so minus a star, but overall a great experience.
Loved the atmosphere, fine cocktails, tasty food and enjoyable bar staff. Looking forward to returning to linger over a longer meal.

Very good restaurant.  Delicious food.  I ate the Nagoya Ramon.  Service excellent. Waitress very attentive,  gave us plenty of time to look at the menu and make our choices and never had to ask for my water glass to be refilled. Chef/owner Tom Power knows how to cook and he is on the job every night. The Washington Post food critic gives both Baby Wake and Corduroy very good reviews.
Great Bar great food. Try pizza and cheese plate. Let Steve fix you a drink. Finish with chocolate whistlepig custard. Love this place.
Happy hour 5-7 is a good deal for after work drinks. Really great bar setup for having a casual drink with a small group.

Pros: friendly staff, lots of space, something for basically everyone’s taste, one of the only places in the immediate vicinity that isn’t either really expensive or really trendy.  Cons: Nothing about the place is special. The beer list was pretty standard, none of the cocktails piqued my interest, and the food we got (burgers and a lobster roll) was just a solid B.  I wouldn’t avoid it, but wouldn’t go out of my way to go back.
Nice staff and great craft beer
The steak was way better than I expected
Fun bar with lots of natural lighting. Staff and hors d'oeuvres are good. Bar is pricy and limited though.

A very welcome surprise! I expected it to be dull and boring, but it was a nice pairing of DC's Go-Go culture and hipster/gentrification 😂. The bar is well stocked with nice bartenders who are pleasant.
Manhattan was amazing!!!
This place has great vibes, very Americana-y with old go-go concert posters on the walls. The food is also great, ranging again from American standards to some accessible Asian dishes.

We arrived in a group of 4. Waited up front so long we felt like we had to ask bartender if it was seat yourself.  He said no, wait up front. After waiting another 5-or so mins, we were greeted by very rude waitress. She sat us, gave us waters, and said I'll be back in a bit (we were her only table). After about 15 minutes she arrives now wanting our drink order and food order. We give her both and she proceeds to put in order. We don't see her again until food arrives 25 minutes later. We start to eat and thoroughly hate everything that was ordered. Waitress finally comes to ask how everything was and we reply, " ehh we are eating it". She shrugs and laughs like it wasnt any of her problem and walks away. We ended up going over to our waitress (because we were being ignored) while she played on her phone more than 3 times to get refills, salt and pepper, and bill. This is the longest review I have ever written because this is the worst service and food  I have ever received. The entire table she was serving (us) was servers and cooks. She was the FIRST server i have ever not tipped and she deserved every bit of it. I would recommend maybe replacing her position to not make the place less unbearable because it was beautiful inside and theres full of great places to go and I don't want another tourist to be utterly dissatisfied over your lack of good help and horrible food
Good food and drink, but only 3 vegetarian options on the menu
Great food!

Now that I'm only about a ten minute walk away from here I come here even more often then before. The food beer and service here are excellent. I especially love the fish tacos and giant pretzels. All of the beer is good, I haven't had one I didn't enjoy.

Loved how the wines were posted on the wall as old school concert publicity. Overall atmosphere is cosy, low-key, clean and inviting. Menu covers all the upscale bar food bases (and will leave you full for hours) and is well executed. Good food and drink, including some craft beer and wines from independent family companies. Best part : music volume low to encourage conversation 💕👍
Charming lighting and great open space for private events
Went for a wedding, very cool space

Amazing quality, wonderful staff and great environment. Have loved everything I’ve ordered in the many times I’ve been. The buffalo mozzarella porcupine is a particular standout, a unique preparation that looks as good as it tastes. The chicken as well is very delicious and worth the prep time wait. A great place to take groups for drinks, the decor and personalities working behind the bar make for a fun and imaginative environment.
This is a pretty cool place. I really liked the feel of the interior. Grabbed drinks here with some friends and they were mixed well.
Went for a party durting Howard Homecoming. Excellent drinks, good vibe.
Long bar. Food is ok.
Great atmosphere, the food is great! The faux rib eye is amazing.

Took a chance based on reviews. Turned out to be a great choice. My bartender Steve had great suggestions on whiskey and beer. I had  the lobster roll and it was very good but the grit fries were an unexpected delight. Great vibe, I enjoyed my visit. I would go again.
The food is always excellent and the bartenders are knowledgeable and willing to put together drinks by the ingredient. Don't ask for that if it's busy, though. That would be rude.
Great service, excellent drink selection, interesting menu options... Don't get smashed and ride the goat.
Great place to eat and drink
Pretentious hipster decor, but the food is seriously delicious. I tried three different entrees which were all good. Plus the chocolate whistlepig custard is well worthwhile for dessert.
My kids LOVE this place! The food and drinks are good and they occasionally play go-go music, so being a DC native in this place makes me happy!
(Translated by Google) Great bar  (Original) Ótimo bar
Just turned up and Baby Whale were happy to accommodate 7 of us, including 4 children. We all had really good meals, the lamb was amazing, service great and a great atmosphere. Thank you
Great ambiance with a very long bar. I ordered the chicken tikka which was delicious, but I do think the menu needs to offer a better selection of dishes.
Had an amazing lamb loin special here, black pepper on the rind, sitting in a chutney sauce that blended perfectly with the juices from the meat.
Drinks were good; food was Ok. A bit pricey for the quality. Love the décor and ambiance. Fun place.
Very good fried chicken. The fries are amazing.
Very cool space. Authentic dc feel, good food and great drinks. Awesome for events and nights out.
Great decor and ambiance, food not so good. Good drink selection though
Great vibe and decor. Great place to go for a drink at their super long bar, but get food elsewhere.
Cute place to grab drinks, have dinner (very date friendly), or host a private event. Great Happy Hour.
Chill neighborhood place with a huge bar, solid food options and an upper indoor mezzanine deck perfect for private events.

Had my birthday party in their upstairs event space and it was excellent. Oriana was my staff contact and she made everything so easy and fun. They have the lowest bar minimum of any of the DC bars I priced, and they don't make you put it all one tab. Everyone can buy their own drinks as if it's a normal bar. The space they give you is fabulous. It looks really nice and cool and the location is great. Also great cocktails. Oriana came and found me at one point to let me know we were a little behind on our minimum. Really appreciated the heads up well in advance so we could meet the minimum comfortably instead of all at once at the end when half the people have left! I have hosted private parties at other nearby bars and they are not always so helpful! The bartender was also great and fun. They accommodated my friends bringing in our own cake and lighting candles, which made my birthday extra special. Thanks!
I feel nourished only watching the decor and sipping a drink. A pleasure for eyes .
Good place to meet friends for a drink, the bar goes on forever.
Awesome atmosphere.  Cool bar.
good food
Nice place
Good beer selection, really cool atmosphere.

I had the Locoro Pupusa. It was pretty good. Fresh locoro flower on top of the tortilla. It is similar to cabbage but slightly bitter rather than sweet. I also had the lamb, antelope & beef meatball casserole. It wasn't really a casserole, but meatballs in red sauce. The texture was smooth (good grind and enough crumb) but too dense and kinda rubbery. The flavor was perfect. The gamey flavor of the antelope made it very interesting but not overwhelming. I think the chef should soften up the texture some how, but definitely worth ordering. The red sauce was delicious, but maybe a little salty. Nonetheless, I soped up every drop with the thick cut, perfectly crusty, rustic white bread. The bartender, older white dude, was 100% pro. He was old school, he'd hang back and swing in to get you another round or pick up plate like a prize fighter who waited for only the best shot. 5 stars for service!
Get the grilled cheese!!

Dropped in as we were passing by.. it wasn't amazing, but wasn't bad, hence the 3 stars. The broth for the Ramen was a bit too salty, though the rest of it wasn't bad. The portions for the meatballs were rather small, not exactly a full meal the way the Ramen was. The drinks were alright, not exceptional, but fun. The cat in the green hat (drink) had a very distinct taste that I enjoyed, but probably not worth going back for. The cheese porcupine was a 5 star appetizer, but didn't make up for everything else. On the other hand, the waiter was awesome!
I had a large party here, around 20 people, and the staff was very accommodating, both the placement of the table and handling a check that large
Good crowd. Good atmosphere. Not overly pretentious. Great bartenders.
Cute place with great food.  I come back quite frequently.  Wait staff is friendly and welcoming.

Atmosphere was very nice. Had dinner and drinks at the bar but unfortunately service was pretty slow (took 40 mins to get a 'faux ribeye' and lobster roll). Also got food poisoning from said lobster roll. Food way ok going down, not great coming back up
Litlle edgy, but great food!
high ceiling. usual American bar on the nicer side.
This place has decent food (pizzas and other bar foods). The pizzas are made in a brick oven. A good selection of beers on tap. Upstairs can be rented out for parties or it will be open.
Great food and service. Cool atmosphere.
Great conference retreat. Steps away from the convention center and it feels like a different world.
Great place for food and beer, good ambiance, great service.
Their dinner is great, but I prefer their happy hour! Where else can you get soup for happy hour, which is the perfect meal on a cold wintery night? Also, the fit out of the building is really cool.

Enjoyed a few cocktails and appetizers with a friend. The service was excellent, the drinks during happy hour were tasty but strong, and the mozzarella appetizer was delicious. I will definitely go back!
Great food and ambiance

Industrial warehouse atmosphere. Extremely loud. Hard to have a conversation with the person across the table. There's not enough room between bar and seating areas. Food took too long to be served. Spring rolls were excellent as well as the Meatballs. Salad was also very fresh. Ribeye was over cooked and dry. Looked like an undesirable cut. Unlikely to return.
Really enjoyed the food. Service has always been great. Interesting space with really large bar.
A great long bar which really means you can spread out. Friendly bartenders.

This was probably one of the worst dining experiences I've had in recent experience. The food, salmon salad and mushroom pizza weren't good. And, the salmon salad which was supposed to be an entry was small even by most standards and the taste was bad. The waiter was rude. Fortunately he surrendered service for our table to the manager who at least did the right thing and comped part of our meal because they got the order wrong. I won't go back.

Great happy hour deals on both bar bites and drinks. Beautiful, modern, and huge space - always busy, but easy to find seats. Food was great - didn't realize until later that it's from the same chef as the legendary Corduroy next door.

With lots of exposed brick and numerous posters that scream "vintage" this bar has a very welcome feel that is a far cry from the many DC hot spots where I feel underdressed when I'm without a tie and jacket.  The bar runs the length of the lower level and there's an additional area upstairs that really gives the place a "larger than it looks" atmosphere.  It's easily within walking distance of the DC convention center (and not too far from the Chinatown area) so there's plenty of reasons to stop in and try some of their happy hour food - especially when waiting for the traffic to die down.  Nice but not too nice - just the way I like my bars in DC!

This place is much bigger than it looks! I was surprised how large the restaurant space is, and even more surprised at how long the bar is! I now understand why it's known as the longest bar in DC. However, the openness does make it feel less intimate.  I met a couple friends here for drinks after work. Their beer selection was mediocre - not a lot to choose from, and the two beers I tried weren't great. We looked at the food menu and decided we didn't want to eat anything here - hot dogs and Asian noodle bowls on the same menu? Seemed very odd. With so many new places opening in this neighborhood, I probably won't be back here.

This place is HUGE...has lots of space, and a 2nd floor.  Went there on a Monday night with a small group and it was just what we were looking for.  Service was great...and I definitely recommend the Chicken...it take 45 minutes, but it SOOOO worth it!

We had a reservation for 8:30.  Arriving 5 minutes late, we waited about 60 minutes for a table.  Service was slow once we sat down.  I ordered the "faux ribeye" which was ok but not great.  The place was very loud making conversation difficult.

First thing you notice other than the pumping go-go music and the fantastic collection of vintage Globe posters advertising Rare Essence shows for $3.00, is the super long bar.  The space is extremely inviting and is just begging for you and many of your friends to come up to it.  Alas I was there solo after a late night at the office, but Baby Wale was still welcoming.  Keeping with the Globe/music poster theme, all of the wines are listed on posters as they would be the next act performing after Chuck Brown at the Wust.  An original and fun idea, and I can’t believe a bar/restaurant hadn’t come up with before.  The menu is simple but great; and I’d imagine all would find something to enjoy.  It is eclectic: ranging from pizza and hot dogs to prime rib and seafood.  I opted for the duck confit pupusas.  Two pupusas filled with delicious duck leg topped with a tangy crunchy slaw.  They were fantastic.  After a conversation with the great bartender Alec, he explained how the chef just likes to cook food he loves and what he thinks is fun.  Luckily I am in agreement.  Highly recommended.
For was OK, but overpriced. The hot dog and spring rolls are your best bets for bang for you buck dishes. Only memorable thing about this place is the chandelier..
